title: Pesticide Storage | From the Ground Up

tasks.task: Manage chemicals on properties in Wyoming.
subtasks: Consider safety by limiting human and animal access.
Focus on label instructions for toxicity, use, and storage.
Store chemicals categorized (e.g., insecticides vs. herbicides).
Keep chemicals in original containers.
Ensure personal protective equipment is stored separately.

tasks.task: Access online resources for chemical management.
subtasks: Visit University of Wyoming Extension webpage.
Review 15 focus points for chemical storage.
Mention of the Jacksonville Foundation at Austin.
Acknowledge support from the town and local platforms.
